[[File:BlackRakata-KOTOR.jpg|thumb|right|200px|A member of the Black Rakata]]
The '''Black Rakata''' was a [[Rakata/Legends|Rakatan]] tribe on [[Lehon/Legends|Lehon]]. The tribe was led by [[The One]], who was deemed a legendary warrior by his tribesmen.

==History==
{{Quote|Those of us who survived have been taken prisoner by a warlike tribe of natives.|[[Soliss]]|<ref name="Star Wars: The Old Republic">''[[Star Wars: The Old Republic]]''</ref>}}
When the [[Infinite Empire/Legends|Infinite Empire]] collapsed, civil wars devastated Lehon. The Black Rakata credited their darker skin to diseases from this time, during which they regressed from their ancestors' technological prowess. Eventually, they were united by [[The One]], and sought to acquire their race's lost powers. To this end [[Black Rakatan Settlement|they relocated]] near the [[Temple of the Ancients]]. For defense, the Black Rakata learned to tame [[Rancor/Legends|rancors]], enormous semi-sentient creatures that were found on a crashed ship.<ref name="KOTOR" />

When [[Revan/Legends|Revan]] revisited the planet, the rival [[Elders (Rakatan)|Elders]] convinced Revan to rescue one of their soldiers being held prisoner in the Black Rakatan Settlement. It was during this [[Skirmish on Lehon|confrontation]] that the tribe was disbanded, the One being killed and most of their warriors being slain by the ex&ndash;[[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lord]]. In their enclave lived a storyteller, who told Revan the story of the Black Rakata. Their nature was opposite that of the Elders: They were cannibalistic and warlike.<ref name="KOTOR" />

